race.comment: PERFECT PLAY (5) doesn't win out of turn but is a very consistent conveyance who is usually thereabouts. A couple of key scratchings now and should be right there when the whips are cracking. EXPRESS PAYMENT (2) is a two-time winner over this course and distance and gets a stack of weight relief with the 3kg claim. Top-three credentials on best form. NAVAL SEAL (3) is drawn to get a favourable run from the inside alley and has the deadly Waller/Maloney combination. Don't dismiss lightly. HEMAN (7) has a solid record at this circuit with two wins and two seconds from seven spins. Makes some appeal. DISNEY CASTLE (9) boasts a win over this mile journey and may earn some minor money.
